devdoc.details: Manage the token assets deposited by components and admins, and invest tokens to the integrated underlying lending protocols.

LogRebalance(address,uint256[]).details: Emit when rebalancing among the integrated money markets

params.percentages: Array of the percentages of the tokens to deposit to the money markets
params.tokenAddress: The address of the token to be rebalanced

addAdapter(address).details: Add a new adapter for the underlying lending protocol

addToken(address).details: Add a new ERC20 token to support in AssetManager

approveAllMarketsMax(address).details: For a give token set allowance for all integrated money markets

approveAllTokensMax(address).details: For a give moeny market set allowance for all underlying tokens

params.adapterAddress: Address of adaptor for money market

params.newSeq: priority sequence of money market indices to be used while withdrawing

claimTokens(address,address).details: Claim the tokens left on AssetManager balance, in case there are tokens get stuck here.

claimTokensFromAdapter(uint256,address,a.details: Claim the tokens stuck in the integrated adapters

deposit(address,uint256).details: Deposit tokens to AssetManager, and those tokens will be passed along to adapters to deposit to integrated asset protocols if any is available.

getLoanableAmount(address).details: Returns the amount of the lending pool balance minus the amount of total staked.

returns.rate: tokenSupply, rate(compound is supplyRatePerBlock 1e18, aave is supplyRatePerYear 1e27)

getPoolBalance(address).details: Get the balance of asset manager, plus the total amount of tokens deposited to all the underlying lending protocols

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

isAdmin(address).details: Check if the address provided is the admin

isMarketSupported(address).details: Check if there is an underlying protocol available for the given ERC20 token.

moneyMarketsCount().details: Get the number of supported underlying protocols.

pause().details: Called by a pauser to pause, triggers stopped state.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

rebalance(address,uint256[]).details: Take all the supply of `tokenAddress` and redistribute it according to `percentages`. Rejects if the token is not supported.

params.percentages: A list of percentages, expressed as units in 10000, indicating how to deposit the tokens in each underlying money market. The length of this array is one less than the amount of money markets: the last money market will receive the remaining tokens. For example, if there are 3 money markets, and you want to rebalance so that the first one has 10.5% of the tokens, the second one 55%, and the third one 34.5%, this param will be [1050, 5500].
params.tokenAddress: Address of the token that is going to be rebalanced

renounceAdmin().details: Renouce the admin from the sender's address

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

supportedTokensCount().details: Get the count of supported tokens

totalSupply(address).details: Get the total amount of tokens deposited to all the integrated underlying protocols without side effects.

totalSupplyView(address).details: Get the total amount of tokens deposited to all the integrated underlying protocols, but without side effects. Safe to call anytime, but may not get the most updated number for the current block. Call totalSupply() for that purpose.

unpause().details: Called by a pauser to unpause, returns to normal state.

upgradeTo(address).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.
